The Chronicle Patrick Chitumba, Midlands Bureau Chief ONE more person has succumbed to Covid-19 in Bulawayo bringing the death toll to 32. The country has recorded 6 406 Covid-19 cases and the recovery rate now stands at 78,9 percent after 13 recoveries were recorded yesterday on a day 18 more people tested positive. All the 13 recoveries were recorded in Manicaland. The country has recorded 196 deaths and one death was recorded in Bulawayo yesterday bringing the provincial death toll to 32. In a statement, the Health and Child Care Ministry said Zimbabwe recorded 18 new cases yesterday, all local transmissions.  